Hi, @Fokko thanks for the review and comments, I agree, this is a cleaner fix, I updated the PR

Since we get the metrics from het Parquet/ORC footers, I wanted to check how the different formats behave. And it looks like this isn't consistent between ORC and Parquet (top one is ORC with exactly the same data):
![image](https://github.com/apache/iceberg/assets/1134248/dc3c0ca4-4fb1-4ab2-b79b-1baee5b1526a)

ORC seems to be closer to what I would expect:

```sql
CREATE TABLE s.l1 SELECT array(1,2,3) AS some_list -- Expect: {1: 0, 2: 0}, got {1: 0}
        UNION ALL SELECT array(1,null,3) AS some_list -- Expect: {1: 0, 2: 1}, got {1: 0}
        UNION ALL SELECT null AS some_list -- Expect: {1: 1, 2: 0}, got {1: 1}
```

So it seems that Parquet and ORC have discrepancies between them.
